@node Keymap setup
@section Keymap setup

@findex vterm-extras-setup-keymap
The function @code{vterm-extras-setup-keymap} configures the vterm mode map in two steps. First, it sets @code{vterm-keymap-exceptions} to the value of @code{vterm-extras-keymap-exceptions} (@ref{Keymap exceptions}), which tells vterm which keys to leave alone when generating its keymap. Second, it binds both the extras commands and several built-in vterm commands to their designated key sequences.

The resulting bindings are:

@multitable {aaaaaaaaaaaaa} {aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa}
@headitem Key
@tab Command
@item @samp{A-C-s-p}
@tab @code{vterm-extras-send-forward-word}
@item @samp{A-C-s-u}
@tab @code{vterm-extras-send-backward-word}
@item @samp{C-H-M-q}
@tab @code{vterm-send-meta-backspace}
@item @samp{C-H-M-r}
@tab @code{vterm-extras-send-kill-word}
@item @samp{C-H-M-s}
@tab @code{vterm-send-backspace}
@item @samp{C-H-M-v}
@tab @code{vterm-extras-send-kill-line}
@item @samp{<backspace>}
@tab @code{vterm-send-backspace}
@item @samp{DEL}
@tab @code{vterm-send-backspace}
@item @samp{C-y}
@tab @code{vterm-yank}
@item @samp{M-y}
@tab @code{vterm-yank-pop}
@item @samp{H-z}
@tab @code{vterm-undo}
@end multitable

These bindings mirror the corresponding key assignments in @samp{eat-extras.el} (@ref{Overview}), providing a consistent editing experience across both terminal emulators.

